props.text:
Welcome, everyone! I'm so glad you're here. I'm your course facilitator, and I'll be guiding you through this semester.

Before we dive into the fascinating world of science, I want to take a moment to set the stage for our time together. My goal is to create a collaborative and engaging learning space where we can all feel comfortable exploring new ideas, asking questions, and yes, even making mistakes! Learning is a journey, and we'll be on this road together.

props.text:
By the end of the course, you will be able to: 

  • Formulate testable hypotheses and design experiments to investigate scientific questions.
  • Analyze and interpret data from experiments and observations, drawing conclusions and communicating findings effectively.
  • Apply the scientific method to solve problems and make evidence-based decisions.
  • Collaborate effectively with peers to conduct investigations and share scientific ideas.
